OL,6,F"We wanted to keep it as a family
OL,7,Fbusiness. It was a stressful time, for
OL,8,Fsure, and from that moment on it was a
OL,9,Fvertical learning curve."
OL,11,FMr Raisey said: "We have always looked
OL,12,Fon Hatchers as being like a family. We
OL,13,Fdid have offers to buy it from us, but
OL,14,Fwe wanted to protect it for the
OL,15,Ffuture, for all the staff that work
OL,16,Fthere.
OL,18,F"Some of our staff have spent all of
OL,19,Ftheir working life at Hatchers."
